In the 1990 FIFA World Cup , Belgium survived the group phase by wins against South Korea and Uruguay ( 2–0 and 3–1 ) .
In the second round they did well against England , dominating the match by periods and with Enzo Scifo even hitting the woodwork twice .
With a persisting 0–0 penalties seemed unavoidable , but eventually they lost in the last minute of extra time after a " nearly blind " volley by David Platt .
Scifo was elected as second best player of the 1990 World Cup after Lothar Matthäus . !
